---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
---

<Base
  title="Visiting Bermuda"
  description="Everything you need to plan a Bermuda trip: getting around without a car, the best beaches, where to eat, where to stay, and what to do. Real information, no fluff."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero" style="padding-block: var(--space-16);">
    <div class="hero__inner">
      <p class="section-eyebrow" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">Visit</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Planning a Bermuda trip?</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle" style="font-size: var(--text-lg);">
        Air visitors spend an average of $2,051 per person per trip.
        Make every dollar of it count.
        <small style="display: block; margin-top: 8px; font-size: var(--text-xs); opacity: 0.6;">
          Source: Bermuda Tourism Authority visitor expenditure data
        </small>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <!-- Featured: Getting Around -->
      <div style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10);">
        <a href="/visit/getting-around" class="link-card link-card--featured" style="display: block;">
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">
            <p class="link-card__eyebrow" style="margin: 0;">★ Flagship Guide</p>
            <span class="badge badge-verified">Most important first</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="link-card__title" style="font-size: var(--text-2xl);">Getting Around Bermuda</h2>
          <p class="link-card__desc" style="font-size: var(--text-base);">
            The single most important thing to know before you arrive: tourists cannot rent cars in Bermuda.
            Scooters, electric minicars, buses, ferries, and taxis are your real options.
            Full guide + interactive transport finder.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--space-4); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ocean); font-weight: 600;">
            Read the guide and use the tool →
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Section grid -->
      <div class="card-grid card-grid-3">
        <a href="/visit/beaches" class="link-card">
          <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Beaches</p>
          <h3 class="link-card__title">Beaches</h3>
          <p class="link-card__desc">
            Five beaches worth your time — including the iconic Horseshoe Bay pink sand, locals'
            favourites, and the quieter spots most tourists never find.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/visit" class="link-card">
          <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Eat &amp; Drink</p>
          <h3 class="link-card__title">Eat &amp; Drink</h3>
          <p class="link-card__desc">
            Fish chowder, wahoo, Bermuda fish sandwiches, Dark 'n' Stormy. Where to eat well
            without paying resort prices every meal. Coming soon — subscribe for updates.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/directory" class="link-card">
          <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Where to Stay</p>
          <h3 class="link-card__title">Where to Stay</h3>
          <p class="link-card__desc">
            Bermuda isn't cheap. The Fairmont Southampton, Elbow Beach, and Hamilton Princess
            are the anchors. See the accommodation directory.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/visit" class="link-card">
          <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Things to Do</p>
          <h3 class="link-card__title">Things to Do</h3>
          <p class="link-card__desc">
            St. George's (UNESCO World Heritage), Crystal Caves, the Railway Trail, Port Royal Golf,
            snorkelling, cliff jumping at Admiralty House. Coming soon.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/visit" class="link-card">
          <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Itineraries</p>
          <h3 class="link-card__title">Itineraries</h3>
          <p class="link-card__desc">
            3 days, 5 days, or a week — what to prioritise at each length of stay. Coming soon.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/directory" class="link-card">
          <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Directory</p>
          <h3 class="link-card__title">Browse the Directory</h3>
          <p class="link-card__desc">
            Hotels, restaurants, transport operators, tour providers — curated and verified.
            Filter by category and parish.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick tips -->
  <section class="section" style="background-color: var(--color-sand);">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Before you go</span>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: var(--text-2xl);">Quick tips for Bermuda first-timers</h2>

      <div style="max-width: 720px;">
        <ul class="prose" style="padding-left: var(--space-6); color: var(--color-ink);">
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
            <strong>No rental cars.</strong> Bermuda bans tourist car rental — one of the few destinations in the world to do so. Plan your transport before you arrive. <a href="/visit/getting-around">Full guide →</a>
          </li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
            <strong>Reef-safe sunscreen only.</strong> Bermuda enforces a reef-safe sunscreen rule at its beaches. Bring one or buy on-island.
          </li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
            <strong>Cash on buses.</strong> Bermuda's public buses accept exact coins or pre-purchased tokens/passes only. No bills, no cards.
          </li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
            <strong>Dress code for Hamilton.</strong> Bermuda has a famously smart-casual dress culture — the "Bermuda shorts" worn in the city are proper, tailored shorts with knee-length socks. Beachwear stays at the beach.
          </li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
            <strong>Drive on the left.</strong> Roads are narrow. 35 km/h speed limit. Take the scooter orientation seriously.
          </li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
            <strong>Portuguese man-o-war.</strong> Stinging jellyfish-like creatures appear on south shore beaches mainly Oct–May. Check with your hotel before swimming.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
